

## Install


### Packages

If your distribution has packages of uim, you don't need compile from source. Following is the list which have package. 

                     * Debian 
                                             * Packages are in sid. 
                                             * apt-get install uim 
                     * Gentoo 
                                             * I don't know in detail, but official packages exist. 
                     * FreeBSD 
                                             * I don't know in detail, but official packages exist. 
                     * [[RedHat|RedHat]],[[FedoraCore|FedoraCore]] 
                                             * Official RPM exists for Fedora Core 1. 
                                             * Source RPM also exists for other destributions. 
                     * SuSE 
                                             * [[[ftp://ftp.suse.com/pub/people/mfabian/9.0/i586/|[ftp://ftp.suse.com/pub/people/mfabian/9.0/i586/]][You can download RPM for SUSE 9.0 from here.]] 
                     * Mandrake 
                                             * Uim is already installed if you are using Mandrakelinux 10.0 :-) 
                                             * [[You can download latest RPM for Mandrake from here.|http://www.geocities.co.jp/SiliconValley-Cupertino/5207/packages-index.html]] 

